@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Video.UI

@*
    Help content for the Video module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Video lets you browse, play, and manage your video library directly from your browser. Stream your personal video collection anywhere.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Browsing Your Library</h2>
        <p>Browse your videos by <strong>All Videos</strong> or use the search bar to find specific titles. The library view shows video thumbnails, titles, duration, and resolution.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Playback</h2>
        <p>Click a video to start playback in the built-in player. The player supports play/pause, seek, volume control, fullscreen mode, and playback speed adjustment.</p>
        <p>Supported formats include MP4, WebM, and MKV with common codecs.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Playlists</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating playlists:</strong> Click <strong>New Playlist</strong>, give it a name, and add videos from your library.</p>
        <p><strong>Editing:</strong> Rename, reorder, or delete playlists. Remove individual videos as needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Favorites</h2>
        <p>Heart videos to add them to your Favorites playlist for quick access.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use playlists to group videos by series, genre, or topic.</li>
            <li>Adjust playback speed for educational or lecture content.</li>
            <li>Search across your entire library to find videos instantly.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
